name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: DOH-Marion joins Marion County Fire Rescue in urging people who opt for a real Christmas tree this year to be safe and responsible. We are sharing MCFR's advice about proper tree care in order to avoid a potential holiday tragedy.  https://t.co/iAskl0jAGu

name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: As prime time for flu season approaches, DOH-Marion is offering free flu shots. Anyone of any age can get a shot, regardless of insurance status. No appointment is needed. We're open 8 a.m. - 5 p.m. at 1801 SE 32nd Ave., Ocala. Or call 352-629-0137 to learn more.  https://t.co/e2eQdJrGpR

name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: Washing hands with soap and water reduces the spread of COVID. But washing your hands also helps prevent diarrhea, eye and skin infections, the flu and common colds. #NationalHandwashingAwarenessWeek began Sunday. Lather up, stay healthy and learn more at  https://t.co/ioEurHtIFQ  https://t.co/DQiBOmkBUH
